	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320171_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Protocol No. 171</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_r_pese">Pese R.</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html"
				>Suwałki</placeName></p>
			<p><date when="1940-02-08">8–2–1940</date></p>
			<p>Homeowner</p>
			<p>Now: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName></p>

			<p>On <date when="1939-10-04">October 4</date> or <date when="1939-10-05">5, 1939</date>, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets"
					>Russians</term> left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>. Before they left the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">city</placeName>, they ceremonially transferred the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">city</placeName> to the delegates of the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">army</term> on <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Magistrate Square</placeName>. Thereafter, bigger <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">army</term> detachments entered <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>.</p>
			<p>The initial two - three days, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> behaved calmly and did not bother anyone.
				They only issued <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1033" type="subject">decrees</term> that when Jews
				encounter a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> soldier on the street, they have to go down from the sidewalk and
				take their hats off. Simultaneously, they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1033" type="subject"
					>decreed</term> for all shops to open.</p>
			<p>The residents immediately opened the stores. Then, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> went into each Jewish
				shop, took the cash from the check-outs, expelled the owners and locked the stores after having taken possession of the keys. They did
				not touch the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term> stores.</p>
			<p>My <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">cousin</term>
				<persName ref="https://yvng.yadvashem.org/nameDetails.html?itemId=10962503" type="victim">Genye Viner</persName> owned a rather big
				haberdashery store on <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Kashtshyushka Street 10</placeName> (now
						<q><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">General Bransch-Straße</placeName></q>). Her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> enlisted to the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">army</term> and was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. And she remained a widow with two small <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> entered also her store, just as they did with the others, took from the
				check-out counter several thousand Złoty as well as all her merchandise. My <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">cousin</term> went to the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> captain and requested to at least return the cash to her since she was a
				miserable widow with two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-327" type="subject">orphans</term>. The captain
				wanted to pay her back thirty Złoty. And when she started crying claiming that she won’t be able to do anything with such a small sum,
				he cynically replied: <q>You can buy a rope with the money and hang yourself.</q></p>
			<p><pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320171_02.jpg"/> I myself had a store for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">candy</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">fruits</term> and wine in my house. The first days,
				the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> did not bother me thinking that mine was a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term> store. Later, though, they came into
				my store and took away all my merchandise. They also conducted a search in my home looking for gold and merchandise.</p>
			<p>Soon after their arrival in the city, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> imposed taxes on Jewish homeowners.
				From myself they demanded 20 thousand Mark, to which I in turn gave an advance of 800 Guilds.</p>
			<p>Whole days, the Jews remained locked in in their apartment because they were snatched up for the dirtiest kind of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> on the streets. They did not even spare
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> also started to go to the homes of the rich Jews and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">robbed</term> everything they could. Many Jews, unable
				to take it any longer, began to flee to the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviet</term> territories.</p>
			<p>In the first days of the month December, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> suddenly issued a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1033" type="subject">decree</term> that the Jews should store up <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> for three days. In the city, there was a
				turmoil. One did not know what this meant. I went into the city in order to go shopping but on the way I noticed how the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> police led Jews, Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>. The turmoil got even bigger. People
				started saying that all Jews will be expelled from the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">city</placeName>
				and sent away to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/858785/wojewodztwo-lubelskie.html">Lublin Reservation</placeName>. I
				immediately returned home and started preparing myself and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824"
					type="subject">children</term> for the journey. Soon, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763"
					type="subject">Christian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> from next door came running to me and
				said that the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> are already coming for me. I managed to escape with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> from the apartment through the
				backdoor and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> in the basement.</p>
			<p>Not everyone was as <q>lucky</q>. Hundreds of Jews with their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819"
					type="subject">families</term> were chased by the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue courtyard</term>. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> did not allow them to take any baggage – hitting the old and weak with whips
				if they were not able to walk fast enough.</p>
			<p>I was laying with my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> in the basement
				until 3am when <pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320171_03.jpg"/> an acquainted <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term> led me out. I did not go back into my
				apartment. The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> had <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-655" type="subject">looted</term> it entirely in the interim and sealed
				the doors afterwards.</p>
			<p>On circuitous routes, I, together with my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject"
					>children</term>, ran away and we met many acquaintances on our way who had also succeeded <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">in hiding</term> from the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>. We arrived in a village located four kilometres outside of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName> and there we <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> for 2 days.</p>
			<p>In the village, we later got a ride and drove to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html"
					>Lithuanian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term> to the village <placeName
					ref="#ehri_et_madani">Madani</placeName>
				<note type="gloss">uncertain</note>. We drove for 2 days because driving was only possible at night. In the daytime, <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German </term>patrols stopped [everyone] and sent them back to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>.</p>
			<p>All in all, we were 50 individuals at the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html"
					>Lithuanian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term>. From the remaining <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName> Jews – around 3 thousand persons were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> by the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and sent off to the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/858785/wojewodztwo-lubelskie.html">Lublin</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term>. 10 individuals saved themselves on
				the last day by running to the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviet</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term>. 2 of them – a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> called <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_maryampolsky_dine">Dine Maryampolsky</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_keltshinski">Keltshinski,</persName> a
				shipping clerk – tragically <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">died</term>. The small
				boat, with which they wanted to cross the river <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3082586/warta.html">Varta</placeName>
				<note type="gloss">uncertain</note>, capsized and they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536"
					type="subject">drowned</term>.</p>
			<p>We, on the other hand, who came to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html"
					>Lithuanian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term>, wandered about <q>no man’s land</q>
				for three weeks in horrible <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">conditions</term>.
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_kotlinska">Kotlinska</persName>, an elderly <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">lady</term>, got <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> there and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">died</term>. We also buried her in <q>no man’s
					land</q>. <persName ref="https://yvng.yadvashem.org/nameDetails.html?itemId=10957658" type="victim">Blumberg</persName>, owner of
				a big glass-store, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-217" type="subject">committed suicide</term>, and his
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">wife</term> went insane from her sufferings.
				Also the dentist <persName ref="#ehri_et_shtern">Shtern</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html"
					>Suwałki</placeName> went insane.</p>
			<p>At the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html">Lithuanian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> me and my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> and they took all the money that I had
				and then sent us back to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Coming to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> wanted to send me off to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/858785/wojewodztwo-lubelskie.html">Lublin</placeName>. But after much supplicating and pleading, the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> took me and my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> back to the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html">Lithuanian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border,</term> and this time I made it to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html">Lithuania</placeName>.</p>
			<p><pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320171_04.jpg"/> Being in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>
				for the second time, I learned that in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject"
					>synagogue</term> there were still 60 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject"
					>arrested</term> Jews sitting to be sent off to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/858785/wojewodztwo-lubelskie.html"
					>Lublin</placeName>. The Jews there literally <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject"
					>died</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term>. At the same time,
				the Jews from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598512/kalvarija.html">Kalvarija</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html">Lithuania</placeName>) did a lot. They sent special envoys to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>. And the last one rescued the Jews one by one and
				took them across to <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuania</term>. In general, the Jews in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/598512/kalvarija.html">Kalvarija</placeName> did a lot for the Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject">refugees</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/757718/suwalki.html">Suwałki</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Signed: <persName ref="#ehri_et_r_pese">P.R.</persName></p>
